  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Abhishek Gupta versus Dinesh Kumar & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_12_479_487','2025INSC1406'); ><font size='4'> <strong>ABHISHEK GUPTA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>DINESH KUMAR & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 479</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1406</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006802025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the facts and circumstances of the case, the Division Bench of the High Court erred in dismissing the Special Appeal filed by the appellant herein assailing the order of the Single Judge in a petition u/Art.226 of the Constitution which adversely affected his not impleaded as a party therein, as not maintainable relying on Chapter VIII r.5 of the Allahabad High Court Rules, 1952. Headnotes&dagger; Allahabad High Court Rules, 1952 &ndash; Ch. VIII &ndash; r.5 &ndash; Constitution of India &ndash; Art. 226 &ndash; Non-joinder of a necessary party &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 03-12-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 14545/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_12_479_487','2025INSC1406','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_12_479_487